---
import Prose from '../../layouts/Prose.astro';
import QuoteList from '../../components/QuoteList.astro';
import { TECHNIQUES } from '../../lib/techniques';

const t = TECHNIQUES.find((x) => x.slug === 'point-of-intention')!;
---

<Prose
  title={t.title}
  description={t.description}
  crumbs={[{ name: 'Techniques', href: '/techniques/' }, { name: t.title }]}
  kicker="Technique"
  jsonLd={[{ '@type': 'Article', headline: t.title }]}
>
  <p>
    Suppose a chart is found with no record of its question, or the geomancer wishes to know what
    the querent has really come to ask. The old books give rules for finding the
    <em>point of intention</em>: distributing the odd points of the chart around the houses to
    find where the question lives, and reading the figures for the matter of another's thought.
    Cattan gives the rules "for pleasure, and to shewe that Geomancie is a wittie Arte":
  </p>
  <QuoteList topic="intention" />
</Prose>
